  "name": "Volatility Compression Breakout",
  "description": "This strategy identifies volatility compression breakouts by calculating the Bollinger Bands width over a 14-period on daily bars. A long position is initiated when the Bollinger Bands width is at its lowest in the past 30 days and the daily close breaks above the upper Bollinger Band.",
  "algorithm_type": "TechnicalPattern",
  "prompt": "I want to design a technical pattern strategy that identifies \u201cvolatility compression breakouts.\u201d For each asset, calculate the 14-period Bollinger Bands width on daily bars and the 7-day rolling standard deviation of this width. Enter a long position when the Bollinger Bands width is at its lowest value in the past 30 days AND the current daily close breaks above the upper Bollinger Band. For shorts, do the opposite: enter when the width is at its 30-day low and the close breaks below the lower Band. Exit positions when price closes back inside the Bands, or if 7-day average true range (ATR) increases by more than 50% from the value at entry.",
